  "response_text": "Here is a healthy, balanced breakfast plan for one week. Each meal includes a good source of protein, healthy fats, and fiber-rich carbohydrates to keep you full and energized until lunch.\n\n### General Tips for the Week:\n- **Prep ahead:** On Sunday, wash and chop veggies, hard-boil eggs, and make a batch of overnight oats or chia pudding.\n- **Portion control:** Use measuring cups or a food scale if needed, especially for nuts, seeds, and nut butters.\n- **Hydrate:** Drink a glass of water first thing in the morning before your coffee or breakfast.\n\n---\n\n### Monday: Greek Yogurt & Berry Bowl\n- **Ingredients:** 1 cup plain Greek yogurt (2% or full-fat), 1/2 cup mixed berries (fresh or frozen), 1 tbsp chia seeds, 1 tbsp chopped almonds, 1 tsp honey (optional).\n- **Why it works:** High protein (20g+), probiotics for gut health, antioxidants from berries, and omega-3s from chia.\n- **Prep time:** 5 minutes.\n\n### Tuesday: Veggie & Egg Scramble with Avocado\n- **Ingredients:** 2 large eggs (or 3 egg whites), 1/2 cup chopped spinach, 1/4 cup diced bell peppers, 1/4 avocado, 1 slice whole-grain toast.\n- **Why it works:** Protein and choline from eggs, fiber and healthy fats from avocado, vitamins from veggies.\n- **Prep time:** 10 minutes.\n\n### Wednesday: Overnight Oats with Nut Butter\n- **Ingredients:** 1/2 cup rolled oats, 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk (or milk of choice), 1 tbsp almond or peanut butter, 1 tbsp flaxseed meal, 1/2 banana (sliced), dash of cinnamon.\n- **Why it works:** Slow-release carbs, fiber (5g+), healthy fats, and steady energy.\n- **Prep time:** 5 minutes the night before (no cooking needed).\n\n### Thursday: Smoked Salmon & Avocado Toast\n- **Ingredients:** 1 slice whole-grain or sourdough bread, 2 oz smoked salmon, 1/4 avocado (mashed), squeeze of lemon, sprinkle of everything bagel seasoning.\n- **Why it works:** Omega-3 fatty acids (EPA/DHA), protein, and brain-healthy fats.\n- **Prep time:** 5 minutes.\n\n### Friday: Green Smoothie Bowl\n- **Ingredients:** 1 cup unsweetened almond milk, 1 handful spinach, 1/2 frozen banana, 1/2 scoop protein powder (optional), 1 tbsp hemp seeds, 1/4 cup frozen mango. Top with 1 tbsp granola and 1 tbsp coconut flakes.\n- **Why it works:** Packed with vitamins, minerals, and protein; easy to digest and hydrating.\n- **Prep time:** 5 minutes.\n\n### Saturday: Whole-Grain Pancakes (2 small)\n- **Ingredients:** Mix 1/2 cup whole-wheat flour, 1 egg, 1/2 cup milk, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/2 tsp vanilla. Cook in a non-stick pan with coconut oil. Top with 1/2 cup Greek yogurt and 1 cup mixed berries.\n- **Why it works:** Higher fiber than traditional pancakes, balanced macros, and a fun weekend treat.\n- **Prep time:** 15 minutes.\n\n### Sunday: Chia Pudding with Nuts & Berries\n- **Ingredients:** 3 tbsp chia seeds, 1 cup unsweetened coconut or almond milk, 1 tsp maple syrup, 1/4 cup raspberries, 1 tbsp chopped walnuts.\n- **Why it works:** High fiber (10g+), omega-3s, and calcium; make a batch for 2–3 days.\n- **Prep time:** 5 minutes (refrigerate overnight).\n\n---\n\n### Optional Add-Ins (to boost nutrition):\n- **Extra protein:** Add a hard-boiled egg or a scoop of collagen peptides to smoothies.\n- **Extra veggies:** Add shredded zucchini or carrots to oatmeal or eggs.\n- **Extra flavor:** Cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla extract, or unsweetened cocoa powder.\n\nEnjoy your healthy week!",
